---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy information for RELab accounts, uploads, and newsletter updates.">
  <div class="content-page content-page-compact stack-md">
    <section class="page-intro content-reveal">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="page-meta">Last updated: April 14, 2026</p>
      <p>
        This policy explains what we collect, how we use it, and the choices available to RELab users and newsletter
        subscribers.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="stack-md content-section">
      <article class="card stack-sm">
        <h2>User Information</h2>
        <p>
          When you register, we collect a username, email address, and password for authentication. Passwords are stored
          only in hashed form. Your email is used for authentication and important service notifications.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card stack-sm">
        <h2>Profile Visibility</h2>
        <p>
          By default, your profile and contribution statistics, such as product counts and top categories, are public.
          You can change visibility to community-only or private at any time in your profile settings.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card stack-sm">
        <h2>Uploads and Media</h2>
        <p>
          Files and images you upload are stored on our servers and included in regular backups. We use uploads to
          display your contributions in the app and for research purposes when you choose to contribute.
        </p>
        <p>
          You can delete your products and uploaded images in the app. If you need help, contact us and we will remove
          uploads and linked metadata on request.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card stack-sm">
        <h2>AI and Research Use</h2>
        <p>
          We may use de-identified research contributions for research purposes only. We do not use personal account
          information such as email, username, or password to train models.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card stack-sm">
        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Newsletter:</strong> You can <a href="/newsletter/unsubscribe-form">unsubscribe</a> at any time.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Account holders:</strong> You may access and update your details, and request deletion of your account
          and associated data.
        </p>
        <p>
          Contact <a href="mailto:relab@cml.leidenuniv.nl">relab@cml.leidenuniv.nl</a> for questions or data requests.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
